CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 23, 1954, pg. 15., reads: "Vice President Richard M. Nixon swung himself around with the crowd during his busy visit in Pittsburgh Tuesday... Center right: at the Nixon luncheon, among others, Atty. Joseph E. Givens, William P. Young, Mrs. Daisy E. Lampkin, Robert Grant, Assistant District Atty. Wendell E. Freeland, Curtis B. Haines, workmen's compensation referee, and Everett McLaine, public relations director, United States Steel... - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group, including Joseph P. Givens, William P. Young, Robert Grant, Wendell Freeland, Everett McLaine, Curtis Haines, and Daisy Lampkin, seated around banquet table, for Richard Nixon luncheon
